{title: Of the Father's Love Begotten}
{subtitle: Prudentius (4th c.) — tr. J. M. Neale (1854) / H. W. Baker (1859) — plainsong "Divinum Mysterium"}
{key: F}
{time: free}
{tempo: 76}
{comment: One of the oldest Christian hymns still sung today. The plainsong melody dates to the 11th century. Sung without strict meter, in chant style.}

